<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,328,784,810]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1891" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1891" box="[711,1044,785,811]" class="Arachnida" family="Oonopidae" genus="Opopaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserticola">
<emphasis box="[711,879,785,810]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">O. deserticola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Simon" box="[889,1044,785,811]" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" refString="Simon, E. (1891) On the spiders of the island of St. Vincent. Part 1. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1891, 549 - 575." type="proceedings paper" year="1891">
Simon, 
<number box="[983,1044,785,811]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="1891.0">1891</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the shape and size of palpal bulb (bulb nearly as wide as palpal patella in 
<taxonomicName box="[967,1084,823,848]" class="Arachnida" family="Oonopidae" genus="Opopaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sauteri">
<emphasis box="[967,1084,823,848]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">O. sauteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but distinctive narrower than palpal patella in 
<taxonomicName box="[346,513,860,885]" class="Arachnida" family="Oonopidae" genus="Opopaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserticola">
<emphasis box="[346,513,860,885]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">O. deserticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the outgrowths on the distal part of bulb (compare 
<figureCitation box="[1178,1303,860,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 A – U" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,167,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[191,1397,167,1849]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 A – U. Opopaea cornuta Yin &amp; Wang, 1984 (B, K); Opopaea deserticola Simon, 1891 (Q, S, T); Opopaea diaoluoshan sp. nov. (C, H, I); Opopaea furcula sp. nov. (E, O); Opopaea gibbifera Tong &amp; Li, 2008 (D, L); Opopaea sanya sp. nov. (F, M); Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974 (G, N, P, R, U) and Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov. (A, J). A – G. Male habitus, dorsal view; H. Male abdomen, ventral view; I – O. Male habitus, lateral view; P, Q. Male left palp, prolateral view; R, S. Female genitalia, ventral view; T, U. Female carapace, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205794/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
Figs 
<number box="[1236,1247,860,886]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="1.0">1</number>
P, Q
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1315,1386,860,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 A – G" captionStartId="11.[151,272,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[218,1346,197,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[208,1365,181,1922]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 6 A – G. Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male embolus, frontal view; D. Female carapace, dorsal view; E. Female scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view; F. Female postgynum, ventral view; G. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale lines: A, B, C, F, G = 0.05 mm; D, E = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205800/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
<number box="[1315,1329,860,886]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="6.0">6</number>
A–C
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[151,228,897,923]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 A – C" captionStartId="13.[151,273,1067,1091]" captionTargetBox="[152,1420,191,1066]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,162,1070]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 7 A – C. Opopaea deserticola Simon, 1891. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palpal bulb, retrolateral view; C. Male palpal embolus, frontal view. Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205801/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
<number box="[151,166,897,923]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="7.0">7</number>
A–C
</figureCitation>
); by the median postgynal depression with smooth posterior margin, but with distinctive triangular posterior margin in 
<taxonomicName box="[384,550,935,960]" class="Arachnida" family="Oonopidae" genus="Opopaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserticola">
<emphasis box="[384,550,935,960]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">O. deserticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(compare 
<figureCitation box="[678,803,934,960]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 A – U" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,167,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[191,1397,167,1849]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 A – U. Opopaea cornuta Yin &amp; Wang, 1984 (B, K); Opopaea deserticola Simon, 1891 (Q, S, T); Opopaea diaoluoshan sp. nov. (C, H, I); Opopaea furcula sp. nov. (E, O); Opopaea gibbifera Tong &amp; Li, 2008 (D, L); Opopaea sanya sp. nov. (F, M); Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974 (G, N, P, R, U) and Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov. (A, J). A – G. Male habitus, dorsal view; H. Male abdomen, ventral view; I – O. Male habitus, lateral view; P, Q. Male left palp, prolateral view; R, S. Female genitalia, ventral view; T, U. Female carapace, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205794/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
Figs 
<number box="[736,747,934,960]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="1.0">1</number>
R, S
</figureCitation>
); and by the larger sized eyes in both sexes (compare 
<figureCitation box="[151,280,972,998]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 A – U" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,167,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[191,1397,167,1849]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 A – U. Opopaea cornuta Yin &amp; Wang, 1984 (B, K); Opopaea deserticola Simon, 1891 (Q, S, T); Opopaea diaoluoshan sp. nov. (C, H, I); Opopaea furcula sp. nov. (E, O); Opopaea gibbifera Tong &amp; Li, 2008 (D, L); Opopaea sanya sp. nov. (F, M); Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974 (G, N, P, R, U) and Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov. (A, J). A – G. Male habitus, dorsal view; H. Male abdomen, ventral view; I – O. Male habitus, lateral view; P, Q. Male left palp, prolateral view; R, S. Female genitalia, ventral view; T, U. Female carapace, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205794/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
Figs 
<number box="[209,220,972,998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="1.0">1</number>
U, T
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="35" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,398,1924]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,353,1008,1034]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Description:</emphasis>
Male. Yellowish brown species with yellowish legs. Body length 
<number box="[1138,1193,1009,1035]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="1.34">1.34</number>
; carapace 
<number box="[1317,1368,1009,1035]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.58">0.58</number>
long, 
<number box="[151,203,1048,1074]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.45">0.45</number>
wide; abdomen 
<number box="[401,453,1048,1074]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.82">0.82</number>
long, 
<number box="[529,581,1048,1074]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.55">0.55</number>
wide. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[826,958,1048,1074]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 A – U" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,167,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[191,1397,167,1849]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 A – U. Opopaea cornuta Yin &amp; Wang, 1984 (B, K); Opopaea deserticola Simon, 1891 (Q, S, T); Opopaea diaoluoshan sp. nov. (C, H, I); Opopaea furcula sp. nov. (E, O); Opopaea gibbifera Tong &amp; Li, 2008 (D, L); Opopaea sanya sp. nov. (F, M); Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974 (G, N, P, R, U) and Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov. (A, J). A – G. Male habitus, dorsal view; H. Male abdomen, ventral view; I – O. Male habitus, lateral view; P, Q. Male left palp, prolateral view; R, S. Female genitalia, ventral view; T, U. Female carapace, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205794/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
Figs 
<number box="[885,895,1048,1074]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="1.0">1</number>
G, N
</figureCitation>
. Carapace sides with finely longitudinal streaks; dorsal area smooth with some hairs at lateral edges. Eyes six, well developed, ALE largest, PLE smallest; posterior eye row straight from above; ALE separated by less than their radius, ALE-PLE separated by less than ALE radius, PME touching throughout most of their length, PLE-PME separated by less than PME radius (
<figureCitation box="[317,419,1202,1228]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 A – G" captionStartId="11.[151,272,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[218,1346,197,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[208,1365,181,1922]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 6 A – G. Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male embolus, frontal view; D. Female carapace, dorsal view; E. Female scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view; F. Female postgynum, ventral view; G. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale lines: A, B, C, F, G = 0.05 mm; D, E = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205800/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[377,394,1202,1228]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="6.0">6</number>
D
</figureCitation>
). Clypeus margin unmodified; clypeus height about 
<number box="[1078,1133,1202,1228]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.75">0.75</number>
times of ALE diameter. Sternum longer than wide, uniform, fused to carapace; radial furrows present between coxae I-II, II-III, III-IV, with rows of small pits; surface smooth, without pits, microsculpture only in furrows. Anterior end of endites with a small, sharply pointed projection. Legs short, thick and spineless. Measurements of legs: I 
<number box="[1308,1360,1318,1344]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="1.04">1.04</number>
(
<number box="[1376,1432,1318,1344]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.34">0.34</number>
, 
<number box="[151,206,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.18">0.18</number>
, 
<number box="[219,274,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.21">0.21</number>
, 
<number box="[287,342,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.18">0.18</number>
, 
<number box="[355,412,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.13">0.13</number>
); II 
<number box="[462,515,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="1.04">1.04</number>
(
<number box="[532,589,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.34">0.34</number>
, 
<number box="[601,656,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.18">0.18</number>
, 
<number box="[669,724,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.21">0.21</number>
, 
<number box="[738,793,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.18">0.18</number>
, 
<number box="[806,863,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.13">0.13</number>
); III 
<number box="[923,975,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.83">0.83</number>
(
<number box="[992,1049,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.29">0.29</number>
, 
<number box="[1062,1117,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.13">0.13</number>
, 
<number box="[1130,1185,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.14">0.14</number>
, 
<number box="[1198,1253,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.16">0.16</number>
, 
<number box="[1266,1322,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.11">0.11</number>
); IV 
<number box="[1384,1436,1357,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="1.19">1.19</number>
(
<number box="[160,220,1396,1422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.37">0.37</number>
, 
<number box="[234,293,1396,1422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.21">0.21</number>
, 
<number box="[307,366,1396,1422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.26">0.26</number>
, 
<number box="[379,438,1396,1422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.22">0.22</number>
, 
<number box="[452,513,1396,1422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.13">0.13</number>
). Leg formula: 
<number box="[710,727,1396,1422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="4.0">4</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[747,758,1396,1422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="1.0">1</number>
= 
<number box="[776,793,1396,1422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="2.0">2</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[814,829,1396,1422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="3.0">3</number>
. Abdominal dorsal scutum strongly sclerotized, punctate, covering full length of abdomen. Book lung covers very small, ovoid, without setae. Pedicel tube short, ribbed, with small, dorsolateral, triangular extensions, scuto-pedicel region with paired curved scutal ridges (
<figureCitation box="[238,329,1512,1538]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 A – G" captionStartId="11.[151,272,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[218,1346,197,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[208,1365,181,1922]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 6 A – G. Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male embolus, frontal view; D. Female carapace, dorsal view; E. Female scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view; F. Female postgynum, ventral view; G. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale lines: A, B, C, F, G = 0.05 mm; D, E = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205800/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[293,308,1512,1538]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="6.0">6</number>
E
</figureCitation>
), scutum not extending far dorsal of pedicel. Sperm pore small, clearly discernible, transverse; posteriorly directed apodemes present. Colulus very small, with two short setae; spinneret scutum present, incomplete ring. Supra-anal scutum absent. Patella of palp greatly enlarged and swollen, shorter than cymbiobulbus, attached to femur subbasally; cymbium completely fused to bulb without suture line; embolus simple, without distinct outgrowths (
<figureCitation box="[581,715,1666,1692]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 A – G" captionStartId="11.[151,272,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[218,1346,197,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[208,1365,181,1922]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 6 A – G. Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male embolus, frontal view; D. Female carapace, dorsal view; E. Female scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view; F. Female postgynum, ventral view; G. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale lines: A, B, C, F, G = 0.05 mm; D, E = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205800/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
Figs 
<number box="[640,655,1666,1692]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="6.0">6</number>
A–C
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,398,1924]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
Female. As in male except as noted. Body length 
<number box="[775,830,1705,1731]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="1.42">1.42</number>
; carapace 
<number box="[950,1002,1705,1731]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.58">0.58</number>
long, 
<number box="[1075,1126,1705,1731]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.45">0.45</number>
wide; abdomen 
<number box="[1318,1369,1705,1731]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.89">0.89</number>
long, 
<number box="[151,204,1744,1770]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.66">0.66</number>
wide. Endites without projections. Measurements of legs: I 1.00 (
<number box="[1001,1058,1744,1770]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.34">0.34</number>
, 
<number box="[1071,1127,1744,1770]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.18">0.18</number>
, 
<number box="[1140,1195,1744,1770]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.19">0.19</number>
, 
<number box="[1208,1264,1744,1770]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.16">0.16</number>
, 
<number box="[1276,1333,1744,1770]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.13">0.13</number>
); II 
<number box="[1384,1437,1744,1770]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="1.02">1.02</number>
(
<number box="[159,216,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.34">0.34</number>
, 
<number box="[230,286,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.18">0.18</number>
, 
<number box="[299,355,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.21">0.21</number>
, 
<number box="[367,423,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.18">0.18</number>
, 
<number box="[436,488,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.11">0.11</number>
); III 
<number box="[553,606,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.87">0.87</number>
(
<number box="[623,680,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.29">0.29</number>
, 
<number box="[694,750,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.13">0.13</number>
, 
<number box="[763,819,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.16">0.16</number>
, 
<number box="[831,887,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.18">0.18</number>
, 
<number box="[901,957,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.11">0.11</number>
); IV 
<number box="[1019,1072,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="1.23">1.23</number>
(
<number box="[1089,1146,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.37">0.37</number>
, 
<number box="[1159,1215,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.21">0.21</number>
, 
<number box="[1228,1284,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.26">0.26</number>
, 
<number box="[1297,1353,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.26">0.26</number>
, 
<number box="[1366,1424,1782,1808]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="0.13">0.13</number>
). Postgynal depression of epigastric area shallow, without parmula, but with a small pit visible through cuticle (
<figureCitation box="[159,249,1860,1886]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 A – G" captionStartId="11.[151,272,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[218,1346,197,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[208,1365,181,1922]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 6 A – G. Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male embolus, frontal view; D. Female carapace, dorsal view; E. Female scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view; F. Female postgynum, ventral view; G. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale lines: A, B, C, F, G = 0.05 mm; D, E = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205800/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,230,1860,1886]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="6.0">6</number>
F
</figureCitation>
). Vulva with a short, T-shaped sclerite, situated near epigastric furrow (
<figureCitation box="[1085,1180,1860,1886]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 A – G" captionStartId="11.[151,272,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[218,1346,197,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[208,1365,181,1922]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 6 A – G. Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male embolus, frontal view; D. Female carapace, dorsal view; E. Female scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view; F. Female postgynum, ventral view; G. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale lines: A, B, C, F, G = 0.05 mm; D, E = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205800/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number box="[1140,1156,1860,1886]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" value="6.0">6</number>
G
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
